12/05/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The government on Tuesday (11 May) presented a strategy to speed up the reform of the public administration. 
President Ion Iliescu says restructuring the sector is an "absolute priority" for the country. 
The main goal of the reforms would be to improve the quality of life by providing public services in line with international standards and increase efficiency by public servants. 
The document highlights a number of concrete measures as well as some new draft laws, which will be submitted to parliament for approval this month. 
(Rompres, Dimineata - 12/05/04)
